news.title: Maharashtra cabinet approves slum cluster redevelopment scheme for Mumbai
news.para: The Maharashtra Cabinet has approved a scheme to redevelop Mumbai's slums into integrated housing projects, aiming to improve living conditions and urban infrastructure. Additionally, a state-wide sewage treatment and reuse policy was greenlit to promote a circular economy and sustainable urban growth.

news.title: Parsvnath Developers, Unity Group lease entire three lakh sq ft retail space at upcoming Delhi mall
news.para: Parsvnath Developers and Unity Group have fully leased the 3 lakh sq ft retail space in their joint shopping mall, 'Unity One Elegante', at Netaji Subhash Place, Delhi. The Occupancy-Cum-Completion Certificate has been received, and the mall is set to open soon. This development marks a significant step for the joint venture.

news.title: Auro Realty eyes $225 million India bond issue to fund acquisition
news.para: Auro Realty, the real estate arm of Aurobindo Group, plans to raise 20 billion rupees via bond sales to fund a significant acquisition, including Hotel Taj Banjara Hyderabad. The company is set to issue two- and four-year bonds with coupons between 11% and 15%, with private credit funds expected to invest.

news.title: Keystone Realtors' sales bookings rises 9% to ₹763 crore in Q2 FY26
news.para: Keystone Realtors reported a 9% year-on-year increase in sales bookings for the second quarter of FY26, reaching Rs 763 crore. This growth was driven by improved property demand. For the first six months of the fiscal year, sales bookings surged by 40% to Rs 1,831 crore.

news.title: WeWork India IPO sails through on last day; subscribed 1.15 times
news.para: WeWork India's initial public offer successfully concluded, achieving 1.15 times subscription, primarily driven by institutional buyers. The Rs 3,000-crore offer for sale saw strong interest from Qualified Institutional Buyers, while retail and non-institutional investor portions were undersubscribed. The listing aims to enhance visibility and provide liquidity for existing shareholders.

news.title: Tamil Nadu allocates ₹1.2 crore for Thiruverumbur Sipcot industrial park development
news.para: The Tamil Nadu government has allocated Rs 1.2 crore for road and water infrastructure development at Thiruverumbur Sipcot industrial park in Trichy. The 125-acre park, located near the Trichy Semi-ring Road, is slated to be fully allocated to a major electronics industry investor. Sipcot aims to secure this investment by January 2026.

news.title: Jaipur: JMC-Heritage plans drone surveillance for violations
news.para: Jaipur Municipal Corporation-Heritage is set to deploy drones for surveillance of unauthorized construction and building bylaw violations in the Walled City. Regular drone flights will also monitor issues like stray cattle and sewer blockages. The corporation is currently evaluating drone companies through demonstrations before a final decision on feasibility and budget.

news.title: Mauda police crack down on illegal sand mining, case registered
news.para: Mauda police acted on a tip-off and raided an illegal sand mining site in Chikhalbodi. Authorities seized a tractor and a trolley full of sand. Sanket Petkule was apprehended at the scene. A case has been registered against him under relevant acts. The police are continuing their efforts to stop illegal sand mining in the area.

news.title: Varmora Granito promoters buy back 2% stake from Carlyle Group
news.para: Varmora Granito promoters have bought back a 2% stake from private equity investor Carlyle Group. This move signals confidence ahead of the company's upcoming public offering. The promoters repurchased the stake for ₹100 crore. Varmora Granito is preparing for a 100% book-built initial public offering. The company plans to use fresh issue proceeds to reduce debt.

news.title: Over 5,000 buyers show interest in two Lucknow development body's schemes
news.para: The Lucknow Development Authority's housing schemes, Atal Nagar and Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel, have seen a robust start with thousands of booklets sold and registrations completed within three days of their launch. The Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel scheme offers 72 flats in Dalibagh, while Atal Nagar features 2,496 flats in Devpur Para, attracting significant buyer interest online.

news.title: Maharashtra forms committee for Andheri’s SVP Nagar redevelopment project of 4,900 flats
news.para: A high-powered committee has been formed to oversee the redevelopment of nearly 5,000 flats in Andheri's SVP Nagar Colony. This ambitious cluster redevelopment project will be managed by a construction and development agency selected through a tender process. The agency will handle resident rehabilitation, monthly rent, alternative accommodation, and infrastructure development. The committee will review project progress every four months.

news.title: Chennai’s third master plan blends housing, transport, environment
news.para: Chennai's new master plan focuses on economic growth, housing, and transport. It aims to reduce travel time and pollution through transit-oriented development. The plan also seeks to boost industrial output and curb urban sprawl. Tamil Nadu is working to become a major research and development center.

news.title: Buying land gets costlier in Uttarakhand, circle rates raised up to 22%
news.para: Uttarakhand government has raised property circle rates statewide. The increase ranges from 9% to 22%, averaging around 15%. This revision follows a surge in construction and land demand. Dehradun's Rajpur Road remains the most expensive locality. The new rates are expected to boost state revenue from property registrations. This move will make residential and commercial properties costlier.

news.title: Land auctions in Raidurg, Hyderabad fetches ₹177 crore per acre
news.para: Hyderabad's real estate market has set a new record with a 7.67-acre plot in Raidurg's Knowledge City fetching an astonishing Rs 177 crore per acre. This landmark auction, which also saw another 11-acre parcel sold for Rs 141.5 crore per acre, signals strong investor confidence and a revival of the city's property sector.

news.title: Master plan in the works to build a brand new city around Navi Mumbai Airport
news.para: Navi Mumbai Aerocity's master plan is nearing finalization by CIDCO, aiming to develop 667 acres adjacent to the new international airport. This project, alongside planned Educity, Medicity, and Corporate Park, will create an integrated ecosystem, significantly boosting real estate demand and positioning Navi Mumbai as a major hub for investment and urban growth.

news.title: Maharashtra government set to amend artificial sand policy this week
news.para: Maharashtra's government is revising its Artificial Sand (M-Sand) Policy this week, focusing on crusher machines to manufacture the sand. This initiative aims to reduce reliance on river sand, ensure construction material supply, and combat illegal mining. The state plans to permit around 50 crushers per district, with royalty concessions already in place to encourage M-Sand adoption.

news.title: About 1,400 flats at Kathputli Colony to be handed over by March: DDA
news.para: Delhi Development Authority (DDA) announced that 50% of the 2,800 flats at Kathputli Colony are nearing completion and will be handed over this financial year. The in-situ rehabilitation project, facing delays since 2009, is now progressing with the concessionaire addressing fire safety and utility connection approvals for the EWS flats.

news.title: MahaRERA orders builder to pay ₹5 lakh for ‘mental agony’
news.para: MahaRera has ordered a builder to pay Rs 5 lakh in compensation to a flat buyer for mental agony and additional expenses incurred due to a delayed possession. The buyer, who booked a flat in 2013 with a promised possession in 2016, had to pay rent for years while suffering from chronic ailments.

news.title: EAAA India Alternatives targets 4x growth in realty assets
news.para: EAAA India Alternatives plans to quadruple its real estate portfolio to 9-10 million sq ft in three years, following the acquisition of three office assets worth Rs 3,000 crore. The firm is also eyeing expansion into warehousing, data centres, and student housing, driven by a demand-supply gap in commercial real estate.

news.title: Real estate transactions evade taxmen using fake PANs
news.para: Tax authorities are scrutinizing property deals across India. Many transactions are escaping detection due to deliberate reporting lapses and incorrect buyer and seller PANs. This move aims to curb benami transactions and unaccounted wealth. Officials are inspecting registrar records and conducting surveys to improve compliance and voluntary disclosures. Accurate data from banks and registrars is crucial for tax assessments.
